UPDATE `cds` SET `report` = 'DNA ligase that catalyzes the formation of phosphodiester linkages between 5’-phosphoryl and 3’-hydroxyl groups in double-stranded DNA using NAD as a coenzyme and as the energy source for the reaction. It is essential for DNA replication and repair of damaged DNA. When targeting one or more enzymes essential for DNA replication and repair pathways, these pathways could be inactivated which might lead to the possible death of the organism.;<a href="http://brenda-enzymes.info/enzyme.php?ecno=6.5.1.2" >6.5.1.2</a>;Yes (max 31% protein identity);Yes (max 30% protein identity);Cytoplasm;No;No;No;"NAD-dependent DNA ligase, adenylation. NAD-dependent DNA ligase, N-terminal. Nucleic acid-binding, OB-fold. NAD-dependent DNA ligase, OB-fold. RuvA domain 2-like. 2 Helix-hairpin-helix DNA-binding motif, class 1. 3 BRCT domain.";No;23 probable phosphorylation sites: 20 serines + 3 threonines;Does not show inhibitors for Treponema or Treponema Pallidum.', `interest` = '1' WHERE `cds`.`accession` = 'WP_010882080.1';
