UPDATE `cds` SET `report` = 'DNA polymerase III is a complex, multichain enzyme responsible formost of the replicative synthesis in bacteria. This DNA polymerasealso exhibits 3` to 5` exonuclease activity. The alpha chain is theDNA polymerase (By similarity).Inactivating any subunit of this complex will most probably take a toll on its functioning. This might affect the DNA replication system of Treponema pallidum.</br>Catalytic activity </br>Deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) = diphosphate + DNA(n+1).DNA polymerase III contains a core (composed of alpha, epsilon andtheta chains) that associates with a tau subunit. This core dimerizesto form the PolIII` complex. PolIII` associates with the gamma complex(composed of gamma, delta, delta`, psi and chi chains) and with thebeta chain to form the complete DNA polymerase III complex (Bysimilarity).;<a href="http://brenda-enzymes.info/enzyme.php?ecno=2.7.7.7" >2.7.7.7<a>;No;Yes (max 38% protein identity);Cytoplasm;No;No;No;DNA polymerase III, alpha subunit. Polymerase/histidinol phosphatase-like. PHP domain. Polymerase/histidinol phosphatase, N-terminal. Bacterial DNA polymerase III, alpha subunit. DNA polymerase, helix-hairpin-helix motif. ;No;32 probable phosphorylation sites: 29 serines + 3 threonines;Does not show inhibitors for Treponema or Treponema Pallidum.', `interest` = '1' WHERE `cds`.`accession` = 'WP_010882114.1';
